This article is a Presidential Memorandum from June 4, 2014, titled "Presidential Determination Pursuant to Section 1245(d)(4)(B) and (C) of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2012." It is addressed to the Secretary of State, the Secretary of the Treasury, and the Secretary of Energy. 

The memorandum states that the President, considering various factors such as global economic conditions and increased oil production by certain countries, has determined that there is a sufficient supply of petroleum and petroleum products from countries other than Iran. This determination allows for a significant reduction in the volume of petroleum and petroleum products purchased from Iran by or through foreign financial institutions. The President also states that he will continue to monitor the situation closely, and directs the Secretary of State to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register. The memorandum is signed by President Barack Obama.